\begin_layout Subsubsection
Slew Rate
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Otro problema con el cual nos topamos a la hora te poner limites a nuestro
 circuito será el Slew Rate (SR), que indica el valor máximo que puede tener
 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\partial V_{out}}{\partial t}$
\end_inset

.
 Esto significa que a una entrada 
\emph on
x(t) 
\emph default
sinusoidal de la forma 
\begin_inset Formula $x(t)=V_{p}sin(2\pi ft)$
\end_inset

 le corresponde una salida 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{out}(t)=\left|H(f)\right|V_{p}sin(2\pi ft+\phi(\omega))$
\end_inset

 siendo 
\begin_inset Formula $H(f)=\left|H(h)\right|e^{i\phi(\omega)}$
\end_inset

.
 Por lo tanto, derivando la salida nos queda la ecuación (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:1_a_3"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{\partial v_{out}}{\partial t}=\left|H(f)\right|V_{p}2\pi f\,cos\left(2\pi ft+\phi(\omega)\right)\label{eq:1_a_3}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A su vez, sabemos que, 
\begin_inset Formula $cos(\alpha)\leq1$
\end_inset

, por lo tanto;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\partial v_{out}}{\partial t}\leq\left|H(f)\right|V_{p}2\pi f\leq SR
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
f\leq\frac{SR}{\left|H(f)\right|2\pi V_{p}}\label{eq:1_a_4}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f\leq250SR\omega\sqrt{\frac{1}{\left(-1571R_{1}R_{2}SR+1571R_{1}R_{3}SR+1571R_{2}R_{3}SR+1570R_{2}R_{3}V_{p}\omega a_{0}\right)\left(1571R_{1}R_{2}SR-1571.0R_{1}R_{3}SR-1571.0R_{2}R_{3}SR+1570R_{2}R_{3}V_{p}\omega a_{0}\right)}}\left(-R_{1}R_{2}+R_{1}R_{3}a_{0}+R_{1}R_{3}+R_{2}R_{3}\right)
\]

